==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Seel
<hw>Seel</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>s⟦aemac⟧l</ets>, from
<ets>s⟦aemac⟧l</ets> good, prosperous. See <er>Silly</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Good fortune; favorable opportunity; prosperity.
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧So have I <xex>seel</xex>⟦rdquo⟧.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Time; season; <as>as, hay <ex>seel</ex></as>.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seelily</ent>⟦br⟧
